<p><strong>Duck breast with cherry gastrique</strong> creates a sublime match, as the wine's inherent cherry notes echo the sauce while its acidity balances the duck's gamey richness. The pairing works because both wine and dish share similar flavor compounds—particularly the anthocyanins that create cherry flavors.</p>

